The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, visited J&D Manufacturing in Eau Claire, Wisconsin, to discuss the growing manufacturing sector and the American economy. He highlighted the creation of 5.8 million jobs in just over two years and the resurgence of manufacturing under President Trump's administration. Pence urged Congress to pass the U.S.-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA), emphasizing its benefits for American manufacturing and farmers. He also mentioned ongoing discussions with Mexico and Canada regarding steel and aluminum tariffs. Pence expressed the administration's commitment to addressing trade issues with China and the importance of fair trade. The Vice President encouraged support for the Ex-Im Bank, which has been beneficial to companies like J&D Manufacturing.